snippet.textDisplay:
Gab taking the deep intellectual approach will never fly when you have colour commentary from the Scottish bombast and banter brigade. Mr Marcotti is a lot closer to the facts though as he has built a reasoned approach about the club Chairman needing to change direction and avoid a dysfunctional relationship given that the chairman had favoured players over coach.

It was a tough spot to be in for Ancelotti and not every team is willing to put in the hard yards in training sessions particularly if they could get a higher salary, better physiotherapy and improved squad depth at another club alongside better training facilities. That is what for example makes Sheffield United a freakish anomaly, grafting and team spirit are rare qualities.

snippet.textDisplay: I watch most Napoli matches and he's sabotaged that team. There's no doubt about it. They have a better squad than under Sarri as they basically have all the same players, minus Hamsik who was already aging. But now they also have Fabian Ruiz, Lozano, Manolas. And you can add Milik who has emerged as top 10 striker in Serie A since Sarri left. So with Milik+Lozano they have two more great options, yet under Sarri's last 2 seasons Napoli scored more with just Mertens and Insigne. On paper their defenders are better too. Koulibaly is now cemented as probably the best defender in the league and Manolas is considered one of the best in the league as well. Yet despite all that Napoli have been playing faaaar worse under Ancelotti. They don't score nowhere near as much. And their defense is likely worse as well, despite him being a defensive "guru". He plays players out of position and in a formation not suited to their previous style. And he insists on interrupting any form his strikers may find with his rotation policy. All in all though when you improve on paper but drop a whole level or two on the pitch that's down to the manager. And one last thing about why it's a big fat NO for Ancelotti to Arsenal...Ancelotti loves experienced players. Arsenal are a young team, they need someone to come and bring out the best of them and get them to make the next step. Ancelotti would only disrupt that, and stunt their growth. Arsenal need to get someone an overachiever who is known to develop players and maximize their potential. Someone like Simeone, Ten Hag from Ajax, Santo, Marcelino, Pochettino, etc. Not this dinosaur.
